\begin_layout Standard
On average, we correctly identify remote job postings 80 pct.
 of the time and the results are fairly robust across samples, ranging from
 70-90 pct.
 in accuracy.
 It is also worth noting, that 80 pct.
 of the joblistings counted as fails weren't 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

true
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 fails, but rather cases where we could not get access to the full job listing
 either due to the link being broken or because Jobindex could not retrieve
 a copy of the full job listing for archived job postings.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Descriptive Analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Graphical Analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We start by looking at the overall trend in job postings published in Jobindex
 in both absolute and relative numbers.
 Figure 3 shows the monthly trend in the number of remote job postings and
 in the total number of job postings on Jobindex in the period 2010-2020.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
placement h
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Remote and total job postings published on Jobindex, 2010-2020
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Graphics
	filename fig1a.png
	width 14cm

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
